eResponse.16
Type:
GPSLocation, simple content
eResponse.16
Name: Vehicle Dispatch GPS Location
National: No
State: No
Definition: The GPS coordinates associated with the EMS unit at the time of dispatch documented in decimal degrees.
E02_15
Usage: Optional
Response
The pattern for GPS location is in the format "<span style="font-style:italic">latitude</span>,<span style="font-style:italic">longitude</span>" where: <br/>- <span style="font-style:italic">latitude</span> has a minimun of -90 and a maximum of 90 with up to 6 decimal places <br/>- <span style="font-style:italic">longitude</span> has a minimun of -180 and a maximum of 180 with up to 6 decimal places
Simple Content
xs:string
Pattern:
 (\+|-)?([9][0]|([1-8][0-9]|[0-9]|90)(\.[\d]{0,6})?),(\+|-)?([1][8][0]|([1][0-7][0-9]|[1-9][0-9]|[0-9]|90)(\.[\d]{0,6})?)

eResponse.19
Name: On-Scene Odometer Reading of Responding Vehicle
National: No
State: Yes
Definition: The mileage (counter or odometer reading) of the vehicle when it arrives at the patient. If EMS vehicle/unit is via water or air travel document the number in "hours" as it relates to the documentation of boat, Fixed Wing, or Rotor Craft in eDisposition.16
E02_17
Usage: Optional
If using a counter, this is the mileage traveled from dispatch to the scene starting from 0.

eResponse.21

National: No
State: Yes
